Reasoning: The paper deals with the algebraic and combinatorial properties of sets of graphs, and their recognizability in terms of finite congruences. This falls under the scope of discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and formal languages and automata theory (cs.FL). The paper also involves the use of logic and model theory, which are relevant to the sub-categories of logic in computer science (cs.LO) and graph theory (cs.GT). Finally, the paper deals with the construction of efficient algorithms, which is relevant to the sub-category of computational geometry (cs.CG).
